casebody.data:
JURISDICTIONAL MOTIONS ALLOWED

93-451. State v. Carter.

Montgomery County, No. 13628. Upon consideration of the motion for leave to appeal from the Court of Appeals for Montgomery County, and the claimed appeal as of right from said court, it is ordered by the court nunc pro tunc, that said motion and the appeal are allowed, effective May 26, 1993.

A.W. Sweeney, Weight and Resnick, JJ., dissent.
